<body lang=RU>

<div class=WordSection1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;line-height:normal'><b><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>What
is chronic obstructive pulmonary disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Chronic obstructive
pulmonary disease (COPD) is a slowly progressive disease associated with
airflow limitation (obstruction) and chronic inflammation of the airways and lung
tissue.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The
disease is also known as</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The disease is also
called COPD.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>In English, the disease
is called&nbsp;<i>Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease&nbsp;</i>,&nbsp;<i>COPD&nbsp;</i>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Causes</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>The main cause of COPD is&nbsp;<b>tobacco smoke&nbsp;</b>;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>prolonged inhalation of smoke generated during the combustion of
biofuels (wood, coal during stove heating);</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>the presence of dust and chemicals in the workplace (among miners,
welders, workers in the metallurgical and chemical industries, etc.).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Who is at risk</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Active and passive smokers;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>living areas with polluted atmospheric air;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>persons with increased sensitivity of the respiratory tract;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>individuals with alpha-1 antitrypsin deficiency;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>intravenous drug users;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>persons with reduced immunity;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>had frequent lower respiratory tract infections in childhood;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>having relatives with COPD;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>persons with hereditary connective tissue diseases (cutis lax,
Marfan and Ehlers-Danlos syndromes).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>How
often does it occur</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>COPD is currently a
global problem.&nbsp;In the world, its prevalence averages 6-20%.&nbsp;The
reasons for this variability are differences in the lifestyle of people, their
behavior and contact with various harmful factors.&nbsp;In Russia, the
prevalence of COPD is about 15%.&nbsp;Although it is now more common in men
than women, the incidence rates in women are increasing.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>COPD occurs
predominantly in people over 40 years of age.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Symptoms</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>COPD refers to
gradually developing diseases.&nbsp;Years and even decades pass from the
beginning of contact with a provoking factor to the appearance of the first
symptoms of COPD.&nbsp;The main complaints of patients: persistent&nbsp;<b>cough
with sputum&nbsp;</b>and&nbsp;<b>shortness of breath&nbsp;</b>.&nbsp;As the
disease progresses,&nbsp;<b>respiratory failure occurs&nbsp;</b>,&nbsp;<b>heart
failure&nbsp;</b>with rhythm disturbances, the appearance of&nbsp;<b>edema&nbsp;</b>in
the legs, exercise tolerance decreases, and muscle mass decreases.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Diagnosis
of the disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Interrogation
and inspection</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>To diagnose COPD, a
patient is carefully questioned about the nature of the onset of the disease,
the duration and severity of COPD symptoms.&nbsp;Attention is drawn to the risk
factors for the development of COPD: the duration and intensity of smoking,
work experience in hazardous conditions, hereditary predisposition.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>When examining a
patient, a doctor, in order to find out what kind of disease it is (if COPD is
suspected), evaluates the respiratory rate per minute, examines the skin,
chest, palpates (palpates) the chest and auscultates (listens) the lungs.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Laboratory examination</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Clinical blood test&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>- in
patients with COPD, there is a high level of hemoglobin, hematocrit, an
increase in blood viscosity and a relatively low ESR.&nbsp;With an exacerbation
of COPD, an increase in the number of leukocytes and an acceleration of ESR are
observed.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Sputum examination&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>.&nbsp;With
an exacerbation of COPD, the amount of sputum increases, the color may turn yellow
or green, and the number of leukocytes increases.&nbsp;<i>Sputum culture&nbsp;</i>gives
an idea of &#8203;&#8203;the composition of the microflora, which is necessary
for the selection of antibiotics.&nbsp;A sputum examination is also carried out
for the presence of Mycobacterium tuberculosis (&nbsp;<i>bacterioscopy,
culture&nbsp;</i>,&nbsp;<i>PCR&nbsp;</i>) and cancer cells.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>The study of arterial blood gases&nbsp;</span></b><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>allows you to assess the level of saturation of the blood with
oxygen and carbon dioxide.&nbsp;With mild COPD, patients have a moderate
decrease in blood oxygen with normal values &#8203;&#8203;of carbon
dioxide;&nbsp;as the disease progresses, the oxygen content decreases even
more, and carbon dioxide increases.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Measurement of the concentration of </span></b><b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&#945;</span></b><b><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>1-antitrypsin&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is indicated in
patients younger than 45 years, as well as in patients with rapidly progressing
COPD.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Functional, radiation and
instrumental diagnostics</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Spirometry&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is a study of respiratory
function (RF) to determine lung volume, expiratory volume in one second, and
expiratory flow rate.&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Patients with COPD show signs of expiratory
airflow limitation.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>A bronchodilatory test&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is
performed to determine the degree of reversibility of airway patency under the
influence of bronchodilator drugs.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>A chest x-ray is&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>indicated
as part of the initial evaluation of a patient with COPD to rule out
comorbidities.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Computed tomography of the chest organs&nbsp;</span></b><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>is the most sensitive and specific method for detecting, assessing
the severity and morphological characteristics of lung damage.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Electrocardiography&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>and&nbsp;<b>echocardiography&nbsp;</b>are
necessary to exclude cardiac pathology as a cause of dyspnea.&nbsp;Patients
with COPD may show signs of right heart hypertrophy and cardiac
arrhythmias.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Fibrobronchoscopy&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is
performed to assess the condition of the bronchial mucosa and differential
diagnosis of COPD with other lung diseases.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Treatment</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Treatment Goals</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Elimination of COPD symptoms and improvement of the patient's
quality of life;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>slowing down the progression of the disease;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>prevention of exacerbations;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>reducing the likelihood of deaths.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Lifestyle and aids</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>To give up smoking;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>elimination or reduction of the impact of industrial, atmospheric
and household pollutants;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>exercise programs.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Medications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The leading place in
the complex therapy of COPD patients is occupied by&nbsp;<i>bronchodilators&nbsp;</i>.
The inhalation route of administration provides direct penetration of the drug
into the respiratory tract and, thus, in the treatment of chronic obstructive
pulmonary disease, these drugs contribute to a more effective drug
effect.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>In patients with severe
and extremely severe COPD, bronchodilatory therapy is carried out with special
solutions through a nebulizer.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Inhaled&nbsp;<i>glucocorticoids&nbsp;</i>are
prescribed in addition to bronchodilator therapy.&nbsp;<i>Mucolytic&nbsp;</i>and&nbsp;<i>expectorant
drugs&nbsp;</i>are indicated in patients with viscous sputum.&nbsp;<i>Antibacterial
agents&nbsp;</i>are indicated when an infection is attached, in the presence of
purulent, abundant sputum, and with mechanical ventilation of the
lungs.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Procedures</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>oxygen therapy;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>physical training programs that include exercises to develop strength
and endurance of the upper and lower limbs (walking, bicycle ergometer, hand
ergometer, dumbbells).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Surgical
operations</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Lung volume reduction
surgery is performed by removing part of the lung to reduce excessive lung
airiness and more efficient pumping of the respiratory muscles. Lung
transplantation may improve quality of life and functional performance in
patients with very severe COPD.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Recovery
and improvement of the quality of life</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Rehabilitation of
patients with COPD: psychological support and the fight against depression,
balanced nutrition, oxygen therapy and physical training.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Possible
Complications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Common and dangerous
complications of COPD:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Pulmonary emphysema&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is a
disease in which the alveoli that make up the lung tissue are overstretched and
lose their ability to contract sufficiently, as a result of which the supply of
oxygen to the blood and the removal of carbon dioxide from it are
disturbed.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Bronchiectasis&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is a chronic expansion
of the bronchi, characterized by a long, often progressive course and a
tendency to purulent complications.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Cor pulmonale&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is an increase and
expansion of the right parts of the heart as a result of an increase in blood
pressure in the pulmonary circulation.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Thromboembolism of the pulmonary artery&nbsp;</span></b><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>- blockage of the pulmonary artery or its branches by blood clots,
which are formed more often in large veins of the lower extremities or
pelvis.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Respiratory failure&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Heart rhythm disturbances&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Prevention</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Critical COPD
prevention interventions: identifying, reducing and controlling risk factors
such as smoking, workplace exposures, and indoor and outdoor pollution. All
patients with COPD are recommended to be vaccinated against influenza, which
reduces the risk of exacerbations of COPD, as well as against pneumococcal
infection, which significantly reduces the incidence of pneumococcal pneumonia
in these patients. COPD is a lung disease that requires mandatory treatment and
monitoring by a doctor, especially during an exacerbation.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Forecast</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>COPD is a disease with
an uncertain course and a variable prognosis. According to the World Health
Organization, it is the third leading cause of death in the world. The
prognosis depends on several factors, including genetic predisposition,
environmental pollution, and comorbidities.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Among COPD therapies,
only two factors improve survival: smoking cessation and oxygen support.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>What
questions should you ask your doctor</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What is chronic obstructive pulmonary disease?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What are the signs and symptoms of COPD?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What is the mechanism of development of COPD?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What is the role of smoking in COPD?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What environmental factors contribute to the development of COPD?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What diseases are differential diagnostics of COPD?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What instrumental and laboratory studies confirm the diagnosis of
COPD?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What drugs are used to treat COPD?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What are the approaches to the pulmonary rehabilitation program
for patients with COPD?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>What are the recommendations for preventing exacerbations in
patients with COPD?</span></p>

